25/06/2003
AMMAN, Jordan -- US Assistant Secretary of State for Economic and Business Affairs Alan Larson said on Tuesday (24 June) that Turkey's compliance with the timetable under the IMF-backed programme is important. Speaking to reporters covering the World Economic Forum in Jordan, Larson praised Turkey's record of reforms, but added that the country needs to meet all requirements under the IMF-backed programme before the United States approves $1 billion in aid. (Anadolu Agency, Turkish Daily News - 25/06/03)
